"""Piecewise-rigid (PWR) with overlapping blocks + grid/overlap sweep.

Two improvements over `register_nonrigid_variants.nonrigid_piecewise_rigid`:
  1. **Sign convention fix**: synthetic-shift test in this module
     verifies that `_block_best_shift` returns (dy, dx) such that
     ``cz[y+dy, x+dx] ≈ hcr[y, x]``, which means the inverse warp must
     sample at ``(yy + dy, xx + dx)``, NOT ``(yy - dy, xx - dx)``.
     The original module had the wrong sign — this module uses the
     correct one.
  2. **Overlapping blocks**: ``overlap_frac`` is the fraction of block
     size shared with the adjacent block. block_size = stride /
     (1 - overlap_frac). overlap_frac=0 → non-overlapping (the
     original behaviour); overlap_frac=0.3 → block 1.43× bigger than
     stride, sharing 30 % of its area with each neighbour.

Per-block accept gate:
  • block NCC must exceed ``ncc_min`` (else shift forced to 0)
  • shift must NOT lie on the boundary of the ±max_shift_px search
    window (boundary maxima are unreliable — confirmed in
    debug_pwr_782149).

Exploration driver sweeps {n_blocks=2,3,4} × {overlap=0,0.3,0.5}
× {max_shift_px=4,8,16} for all 6 subjects on the ws488 target,
reports mean NCC per config, and renders heatmaps + the best config
per subject.
"""
